  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> with the <strong>dried dill</strong>, the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>juice</strong></span> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>dill mayonnaise</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chips</strong> are almost cooked, pat the <strong>basa fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Crack the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate</p>\n<p>Coat the <strong>fish fillets</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then add them into the <strong>beaten egg </strong>and finally press them into the <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium heat </p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>breaded fish</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> into halves diagonally</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> lemon</strong> into wedges </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> to a pot and cover them in plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>\n<p>Once tender, drain the<strong> sugar snap peas </strong>and return them to the pot with a <span class=\"text-highlight\">drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-fish-and-chips-with-lemony-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy</strong><strong> fish</strong> with the <strong>chips</strong>,<strong> sugar snap peas </strong>and <strong>dill mayonnaise</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Garnish with a wedge of <strong>lemon</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
